59 # The type of a variable load is either a value or an UndefVarError
60 mutable struct VarState
61 typ
62 undef::Bool
63 VarState(typ::ANY, undef::Bool) = new(typ, undef)
64 end

66 # The type of a value might be constant
67 struct Const
68 val
69 actual::Bool # if true, we obtained `val` by actually calling a @pure function
70 Const(v::ANY) = new(v, false)
71 Const(v::ANY, a::Bool) = new(v, a)
72 end
73
74 # The type of a value might be Bool,
75 # but where the value of the boolean can be used in back-propagation to
76 # limit the type of some other variable
77 # The Conditional type tracks the set of branches on variable type info
78 # that was used to create the boolean condition
79 mutable struct Conditional
80 var::Union{Slot,SSAValue}
81 vtype
82 elsetype
83 function Conditional(
84 var::ANY,
85 vtype::ANY,
86 nottype::ANY)
87 return new(var, vtype, nottype)
88 end
89 end

91 struct PartialTypeVar

94 # into Const, if the bounds are pulled out of this TypeVar
95 lb_certain::Bool
96 ub_certain::Bool
97 PartialTypeVar(tv::TypeVar, lb_certain::Bool, ub_certain::Bool) = new(tv, lb_certain, ub_certain)
98 end

100 function rewrap(t::ANY, u::ANY)
101 isa(t, Const) && return t
102 isa(t, Conditional) && return t
103 return rewrap_unionall(t, u)
104 end

2459 function merge_call_chain!(parent::InferenceState, ancestor::InferenceState, child::InferenceState)
2460 # add backedge of parent <- child
2461 # then add all backedges of parent <- parent.parent
2462 # and merge all of the callers into ancestor.callers_in_cycle
2463 # and ensure that walking the parent list will get the same result (DAG) from everywhere
2464 while true
2465 add_backedge!(child, parent, parent.currpc)
2466 union_caller_cycle!(ancestor, child)
2467 child = parent
2468 parent = child.parent
2469 child === ancestor && break
2470 end
2471 end
2472
2473 # Walk through `linfo`'s upstream call chain, starting at `parent`. If a parent
2474 # frame matching `linfo` is encountered, then there is a cycle in the call graph
2475 # (i.e. `linfo` is a descendant callee of itself). Upon encountering this cycle,
2476 # we "resolve" it by merging the call chain, which entails unioning each intermediary
2477 # frame's `callers_in_cycle` field and adding the appropriate backedges. Finally,
2478 # we return `linfo`'s pre-existing frame. If no cycles are found, `nothing` is
2479 # returned instead.

4790 #
4791 # 2. If coverage is off, remove line number nodes that don't mark any
4792 # real expressions.
4793 #
4794 # 3. Remove top level SSAValue
4795 #
4796 # 4. Handle bounds check elision
4797 #
4798 # 4.1. If check_bounds is always on, delete all `Expr(:boundscheck)`
4799 # 4.2. If check_bounds is always off, delete all boundscheck blocks.
4800 # 4.3. If check_bounds is default, figure out whether each checkbounds
4801 # blocks needs to be eliminated or could be eliminated when inlined
4802 # into another function. Delete the blocks that should be eliminated
4803 # and delete the `Expr(:boundscheck)` for blocks that will never be

4807 # When deleting IR with boundscheck, keep the label node in order to not

4812 # 5. Clean up `Expr(:inbounds)`
4813 #
4814 # Delete all `Expr(:inbounds)` that is unnecessary, which is all of them
4815 # for non-default check_bounds. For default check_bounds this includes
4816 #
4817 # * `Expr(:inbounds, true)` in `Expr(:inbounds, true)`
4818 # * `Expr(:inbounds, false)` when
4819 # `!is_inbounds && length(inbounds_stack) >= 2`
